said the covers were so similar that readers might be led to
believe that the almanac authorized or in some way sponsored its
use by New York Magazine.
   The lawsuit further claimed that New York Magazine, by imitating
its trademarked cover, had ``impaired the value of Yankee's cover
design and the goodwill symbolized by it.''
